<B><I>Join channel "Holiday" for announcements and ongoing party information.</I></B><br>
<br>
We will be meeting on the Blackburrow Ramp at 9:00pm (EST) for the start of the events.<br>
<br>
<B>Drunken Gnoll Run</B> (9:00 - 9:30 pm EST) - this is really fun! Beware of Arnis, though for he'll kill your Gnoll if given a chance. One Gnoll per participant. Drinks will be provided. Smack your Gnoll until it runs, then try and follow it all the way to Bandl without killing it. If it gets bold and turns on you, smack it again, but watch out - if you kill your Gnoll, you'll be disqualified! Those who can run their Gnoll all the way to Bandl will be the winners!<br>
<br>
<B>Ice River Relay Race</B> (9:45 - 10:30 pm EST) - Have your maps ready - this is a hard contest. Teams of four people will get set up by the three holes in the ice - one at the southern hole, one at the northern hole and two at the center. Tsudao is summoning Coldstones which will be given to the starters at the southern hole. When the race is begun, the starters will jump in the hole and swim to the center hole. There, they will find their partner and pass off the Coldstone. Those people will then swim to the third partner at the northernmost hole and pass it to that person. Half-way there! Now that person swims the Coldstone back to the center hole, passing it to the last person who swims back to the southern start/finish hole. The first three people to hand their Coldstones to Mirabor (the huge Northwoman dressed all in green) will be the winners.<br>
<br>
<I><U>Here are the rules:</U></I><br>
1. Everyone will be given Enduring Breath (Bards can play their version), but NO Spirit of Wolf or Selo's will be allowed! This is swimming skill only. <br>
2. Team members must group together and decide their race order.<br>
3. Only team members and select judges are allowed in the river. All others must watch from above the ice.<br>
4. There is a fourth hole in the ice along the eastern fork in the river. This hole will not be used.<br>
5. There will be floating Bards marking the location of the center and northwen holes. <I>Participants must pass the Coldstones on land only.</I> Once you have your Coldstone, jump in the river and continue the relay.<br>
6. The decision of referees and judges is final.<br>
<br>
<B>Ice Giant Karate Exhibition</B> (10:45 pm EST) - Dalnin will be demonstrating her mastery of the art of body-as-weapon. Don't miss this! Bring your Gnomish Kameras!<br>
<br>
Following the exhibition, those who wish to hunt Mammoth can form a party to go on a Mammoth Mountain Adventure or delve into the dungeon of Permafrost. Those wishing to celebrate with feasting and carousing in Halas are welcome to join us for more games and a chance to win prizes.<br>
<br>
<I><U>Ongoing events in Halas will include:</U></I><br>
<br>
<B>Bawdy Barbarian Balads and Brew</B> - Gather in McDaniels Smokes and Spirits to share limerics (not TOO bawdy, please!), stories or songs an enjoy fine brews and ales.<br>
<br>
<B>Wolves Lore Hunt</B> - Your hosts will be calling out trivia questions to test your knowledge of the Northlands.<br>
<br>
<B>Bake 'n Brew Competition</B> - At the well in the town center. Bring your most unusual ingredients and share your specialties. Judges will be awarding prizes based on originality of dishes and creativity of presentation. Prepare and present your culinary masterpiece to the Chef Mistresses. Categories include "Rare Treat", "Delicious Dessert" and "Full Course Meal". Don't forget the accompanying drink - what are cookies without milk? Prizes will be awarded by the Chef Mistresses.<br>
<br>
<B>Riddle of the White Rose</B> - All of Halas. There will be three rogues wandering around Halas who are Looking For Gamesters (in other words, look for the rogues with their LFG tags on). Find one and ask for a riddle. If you guess the correct answer, you will receive a token. The tokens may be turned in to any Chef Mistress for one of the wonderful baked treats from the Bake 'n Brew Competition entries. <br>
<br>
The event is planned to last until at least 1:00 am (EST) so please try and come out. Visit with friends from Sisters, Brothers and many friendly guilds.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#660000>- </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bcircleofsisters>Circle of Sisters</a><font color=#660000> - </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1>General Discussion</a> <font color=#660000> - </font> <a href="http://www.calsnet.net/fvcos/" target="_blank"><h2>Click Here to View Calendar</h2></a> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

